The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa now stands at 51. Gareth Edwards speaks to Health ministry spokesperson Popo Maja. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa revealed that the number of people infected with the coronavirus has risen to 61. Ramaphosa made the announcement on Sunday night as he announced South Africa's plans to fight the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: Coronavirus cases in South Africa rise to 38 The president has declared the pandemic a national disaster. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.